name: Pompstation | Restaurant in Amsterdam
description:
Bij Bar Restaurant Terras Pompstation kom je voor Wining & Dining onder het genot van fijne jazzy live muziek op de achtergrond

Onze menukaart heeft een ruime keuze uit duurzaam vlees, vis, vegetarische en veganistische gerechten waarmee je een 3, 4 of 5 gangen keuzemenu kunt samenstellen uit alle gerechten.

Op vrijdag, zaterdag en zondag (soms ook donderdag ) zijn er live muziek optredens op ons podium. Meestal Jazzy & Soulful, soms Tango, Bossa/Nova of mooie Singer/Songwriter liedjes.

Het robuuste, industriele, hoge pand waarin Bar Restaurant Pompstation is gevestigd, is gebouwd aan het begin van de vorige eeuw (1912) in de karakteristieke stijl van de Amsterdamse School. De pompen in de kelder zijn nog steeds in gebruik door Waternet.

name: Loetje Oost / Amsterdam Restaurant
description:
Je vindt Loetje aan de Ruyschstraat in Amsterdam Oost. Deze straat verbindt de sfeervolle Weesperzijdebuurt met de drukte van de Wibautstraat. Ons opvallende hoekpand - met mooie, houten pui en het knusse stadsterras - zorgt ervoor dat je Loetje niet kunt missen. Kom langs en neem lekker plaats aan onze bar die altijd uitnodigt voor (nog) een drankje. Of schuif aan in ons restaurant voor een gezellig etentje.

Zeg je Loetje, dan zeg je de lekkerste biefstuk. Op no-nonsense wijze in echte Loetje jus met witbrood, royaal portie friet en salade. Bij ons geniet je van het vertrouwde biefstukreceptuur en het warme Loetje DNA. Bij ons zit je naast deze klassieker ook goed voor vis, vegetarisch en overheerlijke toetjes. Zien we snel?

Team Loetje

We also ordered two starters for the table, the sweet potato fries and the burrata. The fries were slightly salty for my liking, but still delightful nonetheless. The burrata was served fresh and cold, a welcomed change after finishing the hearty steak.

name: Bar Botanique
description:
Welkom bij Bar Botanique; de groene oase in de Eerste van Swindenstraat in het altijd levendige Amsterdam-Oost. Kom na een bezoekje aan de Dappermarkt of Oosterpark langs voor een culinaire expeditie in onze Cafe Tropique!

Bijkletsen met de buren onder het genot van een kop koffie, uitgebreid lunchen met vrienden, sfeervol dineren met je lief en gezellig borrelen: het kan allemaal. Met een prachtige vide, die overigens ook prive afgehuurd kan worden, en een breed groepsmenu-arrangement vinden we altijd een mogelijkheid voor het organiseren van onder andere verjaardagen, vergaderingen en groepsdiners.

I regret that you are writing this review without telling the whole story of what happened. 

You asked us for a private space 'if possible' for your reservation.

Next to that, I am sorry we don't allow people on bare foot on a mat of nails, and filming inside our restaurant and other guests without permission. We have asked you and your group several times to stop these activities, but these requests were not followed up. Other guests were also not amused by these activities whilst having a relaxing lunch, and that's why we have asked you to leave. 
We regret that it had to be like this, but for the next time maybe book a different spot (not in a restaurant) for meditating activities such as these.

Kind regards

They were busy on a Friday evening, but they still accomodated me as a table of one, which I appreciated. What I didn't expect is that I will be sitting in front of the open kitchen, face to face with the chefs :D I was a bit surprised, but went with the flow.
Their head chef was very polite when he greeted me, and talked to me a few times throughout the evening. And for those who went for his special menu, he brought over the dishes, and explained to them what they were.
I had the crayfish cannelloni, which was delicious, and the mille feuille for dessert, which was not only great, but the presentation of it was beautiful too.

Their dishes are designed for sharing with others, so you should probably other two or three in one go (depending on how many people), but one dish for myself was enough.
The floor staff and the chefs were both lovely. Everybody speaks perfect English (which I was very happy about, because I don't know a word in Dutch). And you can see on them that they truly enjoy what they're doing.

The restaurant itself looks very cool too. The service was friendly, welcoming and professional. Our server made some excellent recommendations for all adults and the two young kids with us. I had the 6 course meal with wine pairings which added an extra EU48 (still under EU150 for 6 courses and 4 wines! )

A massive greenhouse located in a park is home to this unique restaurant that truly serves farm-to-table foods (proteins are sourced elsewhere). You will be seated with 2-3 small snacks already on the table with additional amuse-bouche items sprinkled throughout your meal. You can select 3-4 courses for lunch and 5-6 courses for dinner with delicious and creative dishes coupled with impeccable service. Courses are sized and spaced out beautifully so that you never feel full. Servers are very knowledgeable and will assist with wine pairings if you ask. Note that this is a dining "experience" and they book your table for 2.5 hours when you reserve so you can dine at your leisure. name: Vergulden Eenhoorn
description: Discover Vergulden Eenhoorn, a charming restaurant in Amsterdam that combines rustic ambiance with a modern menu. Perfectly located near you, this gem offers a delightful dining experience with an emphasis on fresh, local ingredients. Whether you're looking for a cozy lunch spot, a romantic dinner, or a lively terrace to enjoy cocktails with friends, Vergulden Eenhoorn has it all. Enjoy classic dishes and innovative flavors, making it one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam. Don't miss our unique jeu de boules experience, ideal for a fun day out. Visit us today for a memorable meal in the heart of the city!

As for recommendations here is what I would encourage you to try:
1. The Japanese Gin Fizz is out of this world and my all time favorite.
2. The bitterballen are delicious and are made with good quality ingredients.
3. The roast beef bread was so fresh and the flavor combination adds so much to the dish, however I do have to say that I prefer the bread to be warm.
5. The roasted pumpkin salad is quite refreshing, nevertheless I do think that it tastes better if some salt is added and it would perhaps be more savory with some balsamic or honey as dressing.
6. The white chocolate cheesecake is the only way to properly finish off the meal as it is creamy and savory.

name: The Lobby Fizeaustraat
description: The Lobby Fizeaustraat is a breakfast, lunch, brunch, and dinner restaurant serving inspiring cuisine in a beautiful but casual setting. We also have a bar/cafe with coffee, beer, bar snacks, cocktails, and up to 50 carefully selected wines by the glass. Our space includes two beautiful event spaces for private dinners of up to 60 people, meetings and events, indoor fireplaces for the winter, and a large sunny terrace for the warmer months.

name: Rijsel
description:
Rijsel is ontstaan vanuit passie voor de Franse keuken met een knipoog naar Vlaanderen.
De Noord-Franse industriestad Lille, door de Vlamingen 'Rijsel' genoemd, is niet de hippe en modieuze wereldstad waarnaar veel restaurants zich noemen. Rijsel staat dan ook voor meer dan een naam alleen. In een interieur van klassiek versus jaren '60 modern wordt net als in Lille betaalbaar no-nonsense eten geserveerd. In een ontspannen sfeer is het er tafelen voor iedereen, voor alle gelegenheden en altijd tegen eerlijke prijzen. De gelakte muren, natuursteen, staal en gedekte tafels doen de rest.

featured_reviews:
[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQzdjkyLUp3EAE","rating":4,"name":"Oleksii","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103031882664664080647?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Placed away on a charming little street near the Amstel River, this cozy restaurant is easy to find. The wild deer meat was exceptional--tender, flavorful, and perfectly cooked. It's an absolute must-try. The duck liver, reminiscent of foie gras, had a very rich flavor. They also offer an extensive wine selection. However, the alcohol-free wine served from cans was a letdown, as it lacked the elegance you'd expect. While the charm of the old-school building adds to the atmosphere, the interior could benefit from some renovation. name: Restaurant Elixer
description: Twee chefs en een heel team Elixer sterren runnen Circulaire duurzaam restaurant Elixer met eigen zaal en programmering Open 6 dagen per week vamaf 12 uur. Elixer, onder meer restaurant , proeftuin en programma makers, is een circulair en sociaal kruispunt in de buurt. Ons doel is om goed eten, duurzaamheid en circulaire ideeen toegankelijk, aantrekkelijk en haalbaar te maken; voor en met de buurt. Winst en opbrengsten zetten we in ten behoeve van programmering, educatieve samenwerkingen, buurtprojecten en groene initiatieven.

name: Bar Bukowski
description: Grenzend aan het Oosterpark en het Beukenplein, is Bukowski al 7 jaar een begrip in Amsterdam-Oost. Vernoemd naar en geinspireerd door de legendarische schrijver Charles Henry Bukowski, straalt deze bar zijn liefde voor literatuur en alcohol uit. Overdag een hub voor iedereen, met heerlijke koffies en een zeer uitgebreide lunchkaart, tovert Bukowski 's avonds om tot een echte bar, want in de woorden van the man himself: 'There is always a reason to drink'...

We were unaware of the exact opening time when we arrived at this place. The doors were open, so we entered and sat down, hoping to have a nice breakfast with our two young daughters--one is a toddler of 18 months, and the other a newborn, barely a month old.

We were the only ones in the room since the place has two sections. At 8:53, we went to the counter to place our order. That's when the staff, with a rather irritated tone, reminded us that we had entered too early and asked us to leave. We were just seven minutes ahead of the official opening time, and instead of being greeted with understanding, we were shown the door.

We have always loved the atmosphere here, and it has been a go-to spot for us. But this experience was truly disappointing. The restaurant also has a lovely outdoor terrace overlooking the water, perfect for enjoying the sunny days in Amsterdam.

name: Sushi HANABI
description: The store is located at Leidseplein in Amsterdam, the Netherlands. Our restaurant's dignified appearance, beautiful decorations, and 10-seat counter with a relaxing cypress scent make you feel as if you are in Japan. Watch the rice and fish come elegantly together as our head chef hand-shapes each sushi in front of your eyes. Enjoy this unique Japanese restaurant, which can't be found anywhere else in Europe.

From the moment we arrived, the welcoming atmosphere set the tone for an exceptional evening.

The dishes were a culinary journey, perfectly suited to the rainy weather outside. We began with a warm, sweet steamed custard soup that was comforting and delicious. Each subsequent dish was a masterpiece, from the kingfish with nori and Japanese herb to the bluefin tuna belly that melted in my mouth. Personal highlights included the tuna tartar handroll with warm rice and crisp nori, the rich abalone with sweet sauce, and the prawn topped with caviar, which was so good we ordered it again after the main course.

The attention to detail was impeccable--fresh ginger was constantly replenished to cleanse the palate, and each dish's flavors were thoughtfully balanced without overwhelming the senses. The sake pairing, starting with a light Matsuno Tsukasa Kimoto Junmaishu and progressing to a richer Tsukino Katsura Asahi, was expertly chosen by the waitress and complemented the meal perfectly.

The dessert course capped the evening beautifully, especially the egg custard flambeed with sugar, reminiscent of a delicate creme brulee. Mochi with a light sweet sauce and chocolate powder was a delightful and light finish.

This was my first omakase experience, and it couldn't have been better. The seasonal dishes, the flawless service, and the warm ambiance made for an amazing dining experience. I'll definitely be returning and highly recommend Sushi Hanabi to anyone looking for an exceptional meal in Amsterdam!","published_at":"3 months The staff was so kind and generous but also flustered by this sudden change.

name: Beste Doner
description:
Beste Doner van Amsterdam, al 18 jaar op de Dappermarkt. Bij een uitgevoerde keuring is de Beste Doner de enige zaak die 100% lamsvlees verkoopt hier in Amsterdam! En nog steeds er achter staat dat het zo is. Veel vrolijke klanten die erg tevreden zijn met ons broodjes. Met veel inzet heeft Hasan (eigenaar van Beste Doner) laten zien dat zijn broodjes wel voor het geld waard is. De overheerlijke broodjes zijn nog steeds verkrijgbaar! U bent welkom om een broodje te proeven, dat zal het waard zijn.
Buiten zitplaatsen beschikbaar en eventueel ook binnen het restaurant.
Beste Doner heeft geen andere vestiging. Alleen op Dapperstraat 4 kunt u bij ons terecht komen. Bezorgen is niet mogelijk bij ons bedankt voor uw begrip.

Beste Doner.

name: Benji's Oost
description: Benji's Oost is a cozy Amsterdam restaurant where people can escape from the high-paced city life and find themselves in a peaceful, green oasis combined with an urban feel. During the day, one can enjoy a brunch (lunch & breakfast) menu with a large variety of dishes inspired by cultures and cuisines from all over the world with a tropical twist. Our drink menu consists of excellent coffee from the local roastery LOT61, as well as fresh juices, smoothies, and our cocktail bar serves the best brunch cocktails in Amsterdam. Visit our cozy cafe located at Wibautstraat 196 and experience the unique vibe for yourself.

name: Sushi Fanatics
description:
Please reserve via "Reserve a Table" button on Google Maps for a 2-hours reservation.

Sushi Fanatics is a bunch of crazy people trying to make small-batch traditionally made sushi with freshest ingredients affordable. Didn't imagine you can have Hon Maguro O-toro (fattiest part of Blue Fin Tuna), Hokkaido Scallop and Hamachi at your home? Now you can anytime. We also have handpicked rare Sake and Umeshu for a complete journey to Japan

name: Couscousbar Amsterdam
description: Onze moeders zijn hier de baas. Dagelijks hakken, snijden, stomen en koken zij hun liefde in potten en pannen. Stel zelf je couscous samen of kies uit de favoriete couscous van Nadia Zerouali.

Upon entering the cozy and inviting atmosphere of this charming restaurant, one is immediately made to feel at home. The warm and attentive staff enhance the overall dining experience with their genuine kindness and helpful demeanor.

The highlight of my culinary journey was undoubtedly the scrumptious firin kebab, a local specialty from Turkiye that left me craving more. This delectable dish had me daydreaming about enjoying it daily. Equally impressive was the kelle paca, a traditional Turkish soup that stood out as a delicacy in its own right.

The bicak arasi pide was an irresistible delight, boasting a crunchy, thin crust that paired wonderfully with its flavorful toppings of parsley and onions. Meanwhile, the icli kofte offered an explosion of juiciness within its tender meat filling.

No meal would be complete without dessert, and the kunefe and kabak tatlisi did not disappoint. These heavenly sweets rounded out an already exceptional dining experience. Regrettably, the manti fell short of expectations, proving to be the sole underwhelming dish of the evening.

This restaurant offers a delightful array of flavors and dishes that are sure to satisfy any discerning palate. name: Park Cafe-Restaurant
description:
As if you were sitting in the Oosterpark, but on a very nice chair and just a blink away from a flat white, a good glass of wine or delicious dinner.

Here you can taste the full flavours of Mediterranean and Classic dishes, made with a refreshing and special twist.

Pure, recognisable and authentic. Enjoy your meal!

{"question":"(Translated by Google) Which products at Gangnam Chicken are Halal?

(Original)
Welke producten bij Gangnam Chicken zijn Halal?","answer":"(Translated by Google) - Our own chicken (Drumettes, Wings & Boneless chicken) is Halal, we periodically request the Halal certificate from our chicken supplier

- The chicken dumplings (Chicken Mandu) are not Halal (Halal Certificate not available)

- The vegetable dumplings (Veggie Mandu) are meat-free, but contain a small amount of alcohol

- The rest of our products are produced without the use of alcohol or meat

(Original)
- Onze eigen kip (Drumettes, Wings & Boneless chicken) is Halal, het Halal-certificaat vragen wij periodiek op bij onze kip leverancier

- De kip dumplings (Chicken Mandu) zijn niet Halal (Halal-Certificaat niet beschikbaar)

- De groente dumplings (Veggie Mandu) zijn vrij van vlees, echter is hier een kleine hoeveelheid alcohol in verwerkt

name: tHUIS aan de AMSTEL
description: tHuis aan de Amstel is een eetcafe met culinaire en artistieke inslag in de voormalige "Ingenieurswoning" van de Zuidergasfabriek in Amsterdam Oost. Hier kun je 7 dagen per week genieten van koffie, ontbijt, lunch & diner. Kom vergaderen, brainstormen en elkaar ontmoeten in een van de authentieke kamers of op het terras met uitzicht over de tuin en de Amstel.

name: BAIRES Empanadas
description:
Baires Empanadas & Pasteleria Argentina

Baires is the place in Amsterdam where you can have the Argentine experience eating our empanadas and pastries. With our passion for delicious products and love for Argentine tastes we bring a piece of Buenos Aires (BAIRES) to Amsterdam.
Come by the store and taste them directly or take them home for the road, at home or at work.

!Buen provecho!

As expected, it was not busy at all.

There were plenty of tables and chairs available.
I like the overall vibe of the place. It's very spacious with the high ceilings and it is very cozy.

For dinner I had the "SOFT SHELL CRAB: in tempura with lime mayonnaise and an Asian salad"-starter. It was really good! The crab was crunchy on the outside and soft on the inside.
The salad provided some freshness to the dish.
For mains both of my friends had the "RISOTTO: white wine risotto with mushrooms, parmesan and truffle sauce". Both dishes were really delicious, everything tasted good and freshly made (although the plates were not completely clean,
so we wiped them clean with our napkins).

For dessert I had the "Sticky Toffee Ginger Cake with vanilla ice cream". It was a large dessert for me, the cake was bigger than expected and together with the caramel/toffee sauce, cookie, and vanilla ice cream it's a lot. It was delicious though! The ginger was definitely present.

I will definitely return to this place in the near future! name: The Greek Embassy - Coffee Bar Kouzina - Weesperzijde
description: Your passport to a cultural journey through the vibrant flavours of Greece, right in Amsterdam! An all-day experience of warm hospitality in a cozy and carefully crafted environment or relax outside on our sunny terrace. Enjoy authentic Greek cuisine, specialty coffee , breakfast , brunch, and dinner  in a cozy setting. Crafted with meraki, served with love. Indulge in delicious coffees, freshly baked pastries, and savory dishes that are perfect for sharing with friends and family. We also offer local Greek beers and handpicked Greek wines that perfectly compliment our dishes. Come experience the joy of Greek dining in Amsterdam and make every moment a celebration.

name: Black and Blue
description: Experience an unforgettable dining adventure at Black and Blue in Amsterdam. Nestled in the heart of the city center, this top-rated restaurant serves the finest local dishes with a gourmet twist. Savour succulent steaks, fresh lobster, and a variety of mouthwatering French cuisine. Whether you're seeking a cozy spot for lunch near Anne Frank's house or planning a fine-dining experience, Black and Blue is the perfect destination. Voted as one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam, it offers an exceptional dining atmosphere that will make your visit to this vibrant city all the more memorable. Make a reservation at Black and Blue today!

name: Mister Chen
description: Het restaurant is vernoemt naar de chef in de keuken hij is nog al gek op koken en maakt daarom alles zelf van noedels en dumping vellen tot traditioneel geroosterde speenvarken. Het restaurant is Japans Chinees georienteerd zoals ramen, dim sum sushi en veel meer. In het restaurant zorgt zijn vrouw voor goede sake en lekkere cocktails voor een leuk avond je shared dining. Zomer's hebben ze beschikking over een klein terrasje buiten. Natuurlijk kan je naar je huis laten bezorgen via de bezorg partners maar ophalen kan natuurlijk ook.

name: Cafe Blooker
description: Cafe Blooker, huisje tussen de kantoorgebouwen. Midden op het Amstelplein, op de plek waar vroeger de Blooker cacaofabriek stond. Geopend sinds 2003 en in 2022 in een compleet nieuw jasje gestoken. Bij Blooker verwennen we je met een uitgebreide lunchkaart met internationale invloeden, gezellige after-work drinks met verrassende cocktails, lekkere bites en natuurlijk mag je ook lekker blijven om te genieten van een diner. We hopen je snel te zien!

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNQX0phMGxnRRAB","rating":4,"name":"Michael Komlossy","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104677033579665268520?hl=en-GB","review_text":"With a party of three, we decided to reserve a table at Dauphine. I learned this was a car dealership, which is why it got the name of the Renault Dauphine. High ceilings, a large hall without separation. You have to wait to be seated.
The service was amazing, friendly and super attentive! Leaving no wish or question unanswered.
The food was good, but for the price left space for improvement. I had the Bouillabaisse, missing its freshness and character.
The Caesar salad was ok. name: Brasserie Vrijburcht
description:
Brasserie Vrijburcht is de plek om IJburg voor heerlijke lunch, diner, borrel, high tea, high wine of gewoon een koffie of thee met huisgemaakte patisserie. Wij zijn 7 dagen per week open vanaf 11:00 uur.
Geniet op ons zonovergoten terras, direct aan het water met uitzicht op het Diemerpark. tevens zijn wij foyer voor Theater Vrijburcht.
Ben je op zoek naar een leuke plek voor groepen, neem dan contact met ons op om de mogelijkheden te bespreken. Welkom bij Vrijburcht!

name: Cafe Fest
description:
Cafe Fest is de ideale plek voor studenten om de saaie dag achter je te laten. Drink een pilsje, eet een bitterbal en bestel een gin-tonic of een Moscow Mule(en uiteraard alles voor een studentenprijsje).

We bevinden ons op het Wibauthof op loopafstand van de Wibautstraat en Weesperplein. Ook als je nog snel een scriptie af moet ronden hebben we ruim genoeg flexibele werkplekken uitgerust met state-of-the-art stopcontacten.

Het beste alternatief voor de HvA-kantine vind je bij ons, en bier, heel veel bier. Echt heel veel bier.

name: Breman Brasserie
description: Breman Brasserie is an all-day restaurant and terrace that pays homage to the history of the iconic Lloyd building and features a menu of traditional European-meets-South American food. The bar serves classic cocktails with vibrant flavours and captivating New World wines.

description:
Gelegen op de grens tussen het historische KNSM- en Java-eiland, op slechts een steenworp afstand van Amsterdam Centraal station, bevindt zich Bar & Kitchen de Zuid Amsterdam. Al bijna 20 jaar zijn we de culinaire huiskamer van mensen die in de buurt wonen en/of werken. Bij ons kun je binnen in het sfeervolle restaurant plaatsnemen of op een van de 2 terrassen genieten van smaakvolle gerechten en drankjes in een gezellige gastvrije omgeving.

Onze toegankelijke -en regelmatig- wisselende kaart is een ode aan klassiekers met een moderne twist. Ambacht staat centraal en alle gerechten worden vers bereid. Je kunt bij ons dagelijks terecht voor koffie, lunch, diner of een gezellige borrel. Daarnaast organiseren we maandelijks een pubquiz en het

name: Lunchroom Lastig
description: Lunchroom Lastig in de Amsterdamse Watergraafsmeer is een buurtlunchroom met ruimte voor iedereen. Of je nou komt voor de huisgemaakte Indonesische kaart of de verse broodjes, je met je laptop een paar uurtjes wilt werken of een goede kop koffie (Bocca Coffee Amsterdam) Iedereen is hier welkom.

name: De Jonge Admiraal
description: Locals make the cosy atmosphere in this coffee bar. We have the best coffee of Amsterdam. Well priced breakfast and lunch. We serve homemade soups, cakes and the best omelet. But also tasteful cocktails and 40 kinds of beer, live music performances, pub quizzes and much more.

The rice and meat were dry and hard, I couldn't eat it.","published_at":"3 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-09-24T15:44:21","response_from_owner_text":"Hi Gosia,

Thank you for visiting us. Toko Bersama Oost is a takeaway toko not a restaurant. As a takeaway toko, indeed we freshly made our food every day. Then following food safety procedure and guidance we keep our food cold in our cooling storage & display. When you order our food, you will be given 2 options: 
1. to take the food cold (to be warmed up yourself in the oven or microwave or 2. to be served hot, food will be warmed in our microwave. We believe that most, maybe all Indonesian take away toko in the Netherlands followed this practice as well, when you order a rames menu from them, this is a common thing here In Netherland. 
As for the restaurant, yes you can expect that the food is made by order thus it's hot, hope for your understanding!

Warm regards,

description: Welcome to Amara May, your ultimate Thai restaurant experience in Amsterdam, now offering convenient delivery services. Dive into the authentic tastes of Thailand from the comfort of your home with our extensive menu. Our skilled chefs ensure that each dish captures the traditional flavors of Thai cuisine, bringing the essence of Thailand to your doorstep. Explore our menu highlights like Pad Thai and Green Curry, delivering a burst of authentic Thai goodness. While our Thai-inspired restaurant in Amsterdam is just a visit away, our delivery service ensures you enjoy the same genuine experience without leaving your home. name: Cafe Restaurant Czaar
description: Sinds 2017 is Cafe Czaar een geliefde ontmoetingsplek in de Czaar Peterbuurt, een gezellige arbeiderswijk in Amsterdam-Oost. Bij ons vind je een ontspannen sfeer, ideaal voor buurtbewoners en bezoekers van alle leeftijden. Cafe Czaar is jouw tweede huiskamer: een plek waar je kunt relaxen, genieten van een drankje of meedoen aan een van onze vele activiteiten. Of je nu komt voor een rustig moment of juist de gezelligheid opzoekt, bij Cafe Czaar ben je altijd welkom!

name: Ode aan de Amstel
description:
Ode aan de Amstel, de naam zegt het al! Een hommage aan alles wat de stad en deze prachtige rivier te bieden hebben.

In het voormalig Riva, zit vanaf 1 juli Ode aan de Amstel. Een Restaurant-Cafe met een prachtig terras op het water. DE plek waar je de stadsdrukte even kunt ontduiken en kunt genieten van de rust aan het water.
Dineren met uitzicht op de Amstel kan bij ons zowel op de begane grond, en voor grotere gezelschappen op onze eerste verdieping.

Ode aan de Amstel is de nieuwe Amsterdamse hotspot waar je echt z.s.m. naartoe wilt.

It was nothing short of spectacular. I planned the event from California, without ever having seen the venue in person. The Ode aan de Amstel team made the entire experience seamless and extraordinary.

From our very first interaction, their professionalism and enthusiasm were evident. They worked closely with me to design the event (including a five-course meal) that was both exquisite and perfectly tailored to our preferences for the event. Their attention to detail was impeccable; every course was a masterpiece, beautifully presented as a fine dining experience.

The staff went above and beyond to ensure that our special event went off without a hitch. They executed our vision with precision, from the elegant table settings to the personalized touches that made the evening unforgettable. The ambiance was intimate yet sophisticated, making it the perfect backdrop for a memorable celebration with friends and family from around the world.

The restaurant also did an exceptional job catering to our specific requests, including special dietary needs (where my son and a few guests had food allergies).

In every way, Ode aan de Amstel exceeded our expectations. If you're looking for a venue that combines exceptional cuisine, attentive service, and a beautiful setting, look no further. I wholeheartedly recommend Ode aan de Amstel for any special event--your celebration will be in the best hands.

Thank you to the entire team for making my husband's milestone birthday a truly magical experience. name: Wakuli specialty coffee bar
description:
Koffiebar met lekkere en vers gebrande specialty coffee.

Bij Wakuli ligt de focus op kwalitatieve koffie zonder flauwekul. De beste bonen, supervers en lekker licht gebrand. Met andere woorden, er wordt voortreffelijke specialty coffee geserveerd, maar dan zonder intimiderende poespas.
De koffie van Wakuli is afkomstig van partners uit 14 landen, en wordt geroosterd in hun eigen branderij onder de rook van Amsterdam. Naast diverse koffies serveert Wakuli ook gebak en brood.

Koffieliefhebbers zijn zeven dagen per week welkom.

K.","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100893871697710032830?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Walking into Waikiki Coffee Store feels like stepping into a coffee lover's paradise. The rich aroma of freshly brewed coffee greeted me instantly, promising a delightful experience. I ordered a latte, which was incredibly smooth and flavorful, with just the right balance of espresso and milk. My partner and I recently visited this Argentinian restaurant, and while the prices were reasonable, the overall experience was far from enjoyable due to the staff's behavior.

From the moment we arrived, we felt uncomfortable. The staff repeatedly stared at us, to the point where it felt like they were sizing us up. Before our food arrived, one staff member stood right behind my chair with his hand on it, listening in on our private conversation, which was incredibly intrusive. To make matters worse, while we were eating, I was bizarrely told to switch to another seat for no apparent reason, further disrupting the experience.

When it came to the food, the ribs were overly sweet and sickly, and the salad looked nothing like the menu photos. While it did fill me up for the evening, the quality left much to be desired.

The final interaction was the most off-putting. When the bill arrived, the older waiter made a point of highlighting the tip section and seemed displeased when I chose not to add one. He sulked, walked away without thanking us, and didn't even say goodbye.

This restaurant has potential with its fair pricing and ambiance, but the staff's attitude and the food quality need serious improvement to make it a place worth recommending.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-19T15:32:36","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":[]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR6NWR2SHN3RRAB","rating":2,"name":"Abu Isaac","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115443352950219315272?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Food was lovely. name: Mitts Restaurant
description:
When we opened in 2019, we had a clear vision of what great food should look and taste like.

We've since perfected our passion for pure tastes with classic Eastern mediterranean flavors and source fresh, high-quality ingredients from local and organic suppliers.

But Mitts is more than food - our welcoming atmosphere and cocktail and wine menu are designed to make you feel comfortable and satisfied.

name: De Gastronout
description: Discover De Gastronout, a top-tier restaurant in Amsterdam Oost, where Dutch food meets French bistro. This premier eating destination is a few steps away from you if you're searching for a "restaurant near me" or a "bar near me". Our menu is filled with Dutch and French classics, making us the go-to place for those craving typical Dutch food or seeking a French restaurant in Amsterdam. Searching for the best restaurant in Amsterdam? Look no further. De Gastronout is renowned for its remarkable dinner options and is the perfect spot for a borrel in Amsterdam. We're not just one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam Oost, we're a culinary journey you won't forget.

The Gastronout, located in Amsterdam East, is a cozy gastrobar known for its wide selection of wines, beers, cocktails, and sakes. The menu includes both classic dishes and a seasonal chef's menu, blending French and Oriental cuisines. The Gastronout offers a relaxing atmosphere with great service. Despite the name change from Bar Bistro Bravour in July 2023, the place remains a favorite spot for those looking to be surprised by culinary delights. 

 Well prepared and delicious food
 Veggie options
 Cozy ambiance
 Friendly and attentive staff

What we had:
 CARROT (coconut, hazelnut, miso, yellow curry, lotus carrot, fermented carrot
 AUBERGINE (artichoke, radish, furikake, potato pear, honey and soy sauce)
 IBERICO PRESA (sweet potato, carrot, apple syrup, shallot, parsnip, gravy)
 SALMON
 CREME BRULEE
 WHITE CHOCOLATE (pear, cranberry, Schrobbeler, macadamia, salty caramel)

Amsterdam Oost

If you are in or near Amsterdam Oost - Bar Bistro Bravour is a must place to have dinner.

Our entrees were
Rog - flaky, moist, subtle taste. Our server showed my wife how to cut the fish off the bone which came off smoothly and she had a beautiful fillet.
Iberico - the four pieces were succulent (tasty and juicy), and just the right texture of firm inside and browned outside. The zucchini had a delicious sauce.
Poussin - the meat was juicy and tender, with a fresh poultry (compared to the near tasteless of processed chicken) taste that was accented with the herbs. Served with drawn butter for a rich, smooth finish.
Fries - golden, crisp and crunchy outside, tender inside.
Goat cheesecake - I was thinking a goat cheese would have too strong a taste for a dessert, and this was amazing. The cheese, fruit, and gingerbread crust were in perfect balance. Just enough cheese to have a creamy, sweet taste. Fresh berries. Crumbly and warm crust.

The wine was a glass of Domaine Robert Sirugue (usually by the bottle, our server was willing to sell a glass) - which the server described as "a big hug." The wine and his description was perfect. name: TAQUERIA LOCAL DEALER FOOD INC.
description:
Searching for an authentic Mexican restaurant Amsterdam? Local Dealer Food Inc. is a real family business serving up the true taste of Mexico!

Enjoy our mouthwatering tacos, zesty ceviches, refreshing margaritas, craft beers, and natural wines, all made with authentic flavors and a modern twist.

Join us every Saturday and Sunday from 12:00 to 16:00 for our lively Mexican brunch.  

Come experience the vibrant atmosphere and heartfelt, home-cooked flavor that only a family-run spot can offer!
Mexican Diner - Ceviches ~ Coctails~ Cervezas ~ Natural Wines

name: Restaurant Cancun Amsterdam
description:
At Cancun Amsterdam, we blend the vibrant spirit of Latin culture with the rich flavors of Mexican and Caribbean cuisine to create a unique dining and entertainment experience.
From tantalizing dishes prepared with fresh, authentic ingredients to dynamic events featuring the best in salsa, bachata, and Latin music, we're dedicated to bringing the essence of Cancun to Amsterdam.
Join us for a journey of taste, rhythm, and unforgettable moments.

Where Flavors and Rhythms Meet.

name: Risto Enoteca PepeNero
description:
Discover a gem in Amsterdam's dining scene, Risto Enoteca PepeNero. A blend of fine and casual dining, PepeNero offers a mouth-watering selection of the best Italian food in Amsterdam. Experience the vibrant flavors of the Italian cuisine, reimagined with a unique Southern Italian twist. From the freshest pasta in Amsterdam to exquisite local dishes, PepeNero is a must-visit for food lovers. Enjoy a memorable dining experience in the heart of Amsterdam, perfect for those craving Italiaan food.
Whether you're visiting Carre or another theater nearby, we're happy to serve you a delicious dinner before attending the show. Let us know when you enter and we'll make sure you're done in time!

Disappointing at best. I genuinely don't understand how it gets such a high review.

Firstly it took 1,5 hrs to get our food once ordered. The bread we were served was hard and dried out.
Since it was taking so long, we asked for a salad and they said 'yes of course', but we were served a plate of vegetable antipasti instead.
When we asked for some vinegar for our bread, we were unpleasantly surprised when we were given chili oil instead.
After about an hour of waiting, we asked them where our food was and the waitress said they were waiting to serve our pasta until we were done the "salad" even though there had been nothing but a small piece of arugula left on the plate for the last 20 min.
While we continued to wait, the inside was noisy and hard to have a conversation. Every few minutes the background music was interrupted by ads for Albert Heijn (at the price of the food they can't just pay for Spotify premium?...)
Once we got the food, it came out all at different times, with one of our guests getting his food 15 minutes later than everyone else.
Plus, EU25 for pasta that takes 1,5hrs is extortionate. Ultimately, maybe it would have tasted better if we didn't wait so long, but in the end it tasted rather unremarkable. On the upside, the wine was pretty decent, but we needed it. The staff was really friendly, helpful and all Italians which gave it a nice authentic atmosphere.
The aperitivo to start with was great - an amazing Aperol Spritz and the alcohol free Gin Tonic was also nice.
The food overall was absolutely amazing. We tried the burrata, the pinsa (bruschetta like bread), the spaghetti out of the parmesan wheel, ravioli and the octopus. Everything was super tasty and fresh, but if we had to select our winners it would be the spaghetti (the sauce was just incredible) and the octopus. If we want to complain on anything, it would be the bread that came prior to the dishes which seemed a bit hard but honestly, the food throughout the night was amazing!

I dived into the Alba and Foer Restaurant collab in Amsterdam, where chefs Steven Broere and George Kataras took us on a culinary joyride. Each course was like a little masterpiece--super unique, gorgeously presented, and absolutely delicious.

We kicked off with an onion broth mixed with angelica oil and black currant, light yet aromatic, teasing my taste buds for what was to come. Next, the potato bread topped with turbot roe and bronze fennel? Game changer! One bite, and I was hooked--the perfect blend of richness and texture.

The charred veggies with celeriac and horseradish had this smoky, spicy kick that was just awesome. And then, BBQ mackerel with plums and chorizo oil? Talk about bold flavors! The balance of smoky fish, sweet plum, and a hint of heat made it unforgettable.

But the surprises didn't stop there--the salsify with coffee kombucha and hazelnut brought a cool earthy twist, and the chicken paired with hen of the woods mushrooms and blackberry tasted like a cozy forest picnic in autumn.

Then came the grand finale: a blood orange and Sichuan pepper donut that was as playful as it was refreshing. Sweet, spicy, and just the right amount of zing--a perfect end to this flavor-packed journey. And don't even get me started on the wine pairings--they weren't just good, they were spot-on with each dish, enhancing every flavor without stealing the spotlight.

Highly recommend this for anyone looking for a memorable, inventive dining experience in Amsterdam!","published_at":"2 months name: Restaurant Nomads
description:
Uniek uiteten in Amsterdam met NOMADS, de reizende wereldkeuken! Geniet van ons zonnige terras met een prachtig uitzicht op het water of ons stijlvolle interieur.
Bij NOMADS, gaan we als echte nomaden de wereld rond om onontdekte smaken, spannende producten en authentieke recepten te vinden. Tijdens onze jaarlijkse reis struinen wij lokale markten af, volgen kookworkshops en vullen onze backpacks vullen met bijzondere producten.

Gedurende 9 tot 12 maanden brengen we het mooiste van onze reizen naar je toe. Elk gerecht heeft een eigen verhaal en oorsprong, en ons gepassioneerde personeel deelt dit graag met je. Ga mee op culinaire reis en ontdek al het bijzonders dat onze bestemmingen te bieden hebben. - NOMADS is perfect voor groepen

name: Boi Boi
description: Boi Boi Thaifood challenges you to dare eat the Far East. This is where the flag with the aggressive monkey flies. The monkey of Boi Boi, the Thai restaurant on the Dapper street market. Our flag combines different influences. The interior feels like a Japanese izakaya with the friendly warmth of Thailand. Our guests are the current Dappermarket visitors, young starters and tourists who dare to step off the beaten track. There is more to Amsterdam than the Leidseplein and Dam square. A place you will only find if you know the locals. We offer vegan, vegetarian and meat and fish dishes and also have a take out and delivery address.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNEaDg3bnNRRRAB","rating":5,"name":"KN IWN","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113234314517691749806?hl=en-GB","review_text":"My friends and I found this place coincidentally after our yoga class so we gave it a try. The dish we ordered came out just OK so we asked additional chilies and fish sauce to spice it up and then the history starts! The chef (Mr.Kay/Candy) came out to served us so we had a bit of conversations. He mentioned that he will cook it again as the authentic taste but we refused and wanted to try next time. Later he served us another dish as a compliment and it tastes like home. We really appreciate his kindness. So, we would like to give it a try again.

After a few weeks, my friends and I revisited the restaurant again and we ordered the food a week in advance! Some of them are not even in the menu but they were very kind to prepare them all  for us. The food was so so good, very spicy and tasteful. All my Thai friends and I feel like we are having Isan food in Thailand. The staffs welcomed us very warmly. The dessert is so good especially the mochi ice cream!

The chef let us try his Sa-to which is a rice wine that popular in Laos and NE region of Thailand. Oh also, the rice whiskey with some herbs. Even serve us the tea from Laos before we leave. Their services is beyond our expectations. We are really happy and enjoy our time there.

We will definitely visit here again and try more dish. We always like to start off with a cold brewski and off course they had 2 cold Singha's for us. Make reservations now! We started with some fresh Thai spring rolls and they were truly fresh, handmade and delicious. Must try! Then my wife had the Pad Krapao and she ate everything, and I had the Chicken Paneng Curry. I am always afraid that they don't make it spicy enough, but the level of spiciness was just right for me. The chef is from Laos and everything is freshly made. Go there! name: The Harbour Club Amsterdam - East
description:
Een unieke locatie in Amsterdam met internationale allure, een sprankelende sfeer en buitengewoon fantastisch eten. Een blend van Miami, Barcelona en de Cote d'Azur: een industriele locatie - een oude wijnterminal - turned fashionable chic. Kom langs en laat je verrassen door de immense ruimte (2200m2), het 'top notch gestylde' interieur, de zes meter lange visvitrine, de hoogwaardige kookkunsten en de zestien meter lange muurschildering van neo popart kunstenaar Selwyn Senatori.

Een bezoek aan The Harbour Club staat garant voor puur en intens genieten. Hoogstaande kookkunsten gemixt met een tikkeltje eigenwijsheid, maar wel met oog voor detail.

name: Alba Restaurant & Wijnbar
description: Alba Restaurant & Wijnbar - offers a casual fine dining experience in a relaxed atmosphere. Located in Amsterdam Oost, our creative seasonal menu, crafted from the freshest ingredients, pairs perfectly with our extensive wine list. Alba's cozy ambiance inside is ideal for an intimate dinner or a special group celebration. Our large sunny terrace outside offers a perfect outdoor dining option, where you can enjoy a romantic dinner or a night out with family and friends. With diverse dishes and exceptional wines, Alba restaurant in Amsterdam promises an unforgettable dining experience. Discover why Alba is the top choice for restaurant and wine bar enthusiasts in Amsterdam.

[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQzekxHU1V3EAE","rating":5,"name":"Monica M.","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113944174080037868402?hl=en-GB","review_text":"I came to this place on my visit to Amsterdam in mid-October 2024.

The first time I visited was in a slight panic trying to find takeaway places to order a quick late night meal that catered for my allergens.  By that point, I'd walked around for about 30 minutes trying to find a place with no luck, until I came to Hearth on 11 Oct 2024.  They'd sadly JUST stopped food service when I arrived, but the lovely owner, Marcus, took pity on my plight and offered some excellent gluten free and vegan quinoa sushi with dressing for free.  I was amazed by his wonderful generosity that I made a point to come and visit to try the menu out properly when my friend from London arrived.

And that we did.  We visited on Sunday 13 October as walk-ins and everything from the food (presentation and flavour) the non-alcoholic cocktails, the ambience, and the service was nothing short of amazing.  Unfortunately Marcus wasn't there the night I visited as a sit-down guest, but I did offer him one promise...this review, so I send my heartfelt gratitude for his kindness and generosity.  He has a wonderful business.  The food was amazing...I couldn't fault the flavours and textures.  Please do yourself a favour and go - you will not be disappointed by the inventiveness of the dishes and drinks at this place.

Thank you again! name: De Kop van Oost
description: In de keuken van De Kop van Oost ontmoeten Franse tradities frisse, energieke internationale invloeden. De menukaart wisselt regelmatig en zet verse, pure ingredienten centraal. Onze zorgvuldig samengestelde wijnkaart biedt een prachtige mix van klassiekers en verrassende nieuwe ontdekkingen uit heel Europa.
